  "body": "### Version of Hardhat\r\n\r\n2.12.6\r\n\r\n### What happened?\r\n\r\nI've created a new project using pnpm/pnpx: \r\n\r\n```\r\npnpx hardhat\r\n```\r\nBesides some 'deprecated' warnings and this strange message log like if npm has been executed in spite of pnpm, everything seems fine `npm install --save-dev hardhat@^2.12.6 @nomicfoundation/hardhat-toolbox@^2.0.0`.\r\n\r\nHowever, when I try to compile with `pnpx hardhat compile`, I got the error message: `HH12: Trying to use a non-local installation of Hardhat, which is not supported`.\r\n\r\nThe release v2.12.6 introduced the support to pnpm, didn't it?\r\n\r\n### Minimal reproduction steps\r\n\r\n> pnpx hardhat \r\nChoose Create a TypeScript project\r\n> pnpx hardhat compile\r\n\r\n### Search terms\r\n\r\npnpm ",
